Yobe State government has declared the cholera outbreak over in the state over, saying no cholera case has been reported for three weeks even as samples from suspected cases had tested negative. The state Commissioner for Health, Dr Mohammed Bello Kawuwa, said this in Damaturu yesterday. He said the outbreak was first reported on March 28, 2018 in Gashua, Bade local government council, and subsequently spread to Yusufari, Jakusko, Karasuwa and Bursari local government areas.